<hr>
<div class='commentinfo comment_'>
2005-05-18 20:55:39 (3300 days ago)
<div id='contact-3829'><span class='name'>Matt Schafer</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/3829/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
Not sure why people refer to this run as a &quot;safe&quot; or a &quot;beginner run&quot;. Ran it<br/>
at 4.9' this past weekend. Main river left channel of the first falls was easy to boof; but major<br/>
recirc if you mess up - I give it a III+.<br/>
<br/>
Ran the river right spout on the second drop. Easy and consequence free if you mess up. I give it a<br/>
III-. Then we ran down another little III- rapid.<br/>
<br/>
Next we came to Hamburger Helper. At that level a solid Class V. This rapid (including the sneak)<br/>
is probably as tough as anything I have paddled on Upper Gauley or Upper Yough at normal flows.<br/>
Dangerous recirc and pin potential. Ran it through the sneak and had to roll up (3 times).<br/>
<br/>
Then we came to Twist and Shout. Scouted it for a while and decided not to run it (even though I<br/>
have ran it seveal times before without problem). There was a big pillow rock near the bottom of<br/>
the drop that sent about 45% of the river into a bad pinning &quot;room of doom&quot; situation. It<br/>
looked really nasty. Have to say Class V at that level.<br/>
<br/>
Overall, I'd say Valley Falls is a III-V run at 4.9'. </div>
</td>
</tr>
